So we did everything we could to keep going.4 years later, we achieved our new goal of visiting 100 countries and all 7 continents. column8: Gone With the Wynns|the Wynns|Sailing|Catamaran|Sailboat|Sail Around the World|Diving|Cruising|Nikki and Jason Wynn|Blue Water Cruising|Ocean|Sailing for Beginners|Circumnavigation|Life on a Yacht|Living on a Yacht|Boating|Boat life|lifestyle|curiosity|free diving|travel|adventure|off grid|tiny house|living on a sailboat|Gone With The Wind Sailing|self reliance|sustainablity|Apo Reef|Sailing Philippines|Sailing to Palawan
column16: We set sail for what we thought would be a leisurely 250 nm sail from Subic to the northern part of Palawan. ¬†How na√Øve!¬† Mother nature had a full mix of wind and waves in store for us.¬† It felt like we were learning how to sail all over again.‚ù§ Join Our Crew! ‚ù§ For exclusive content, behind the scenes & Q&A's: http://bit.ly/patreon-wynn https://www.gonewiththewynns.com‚òùBehind the Scenes, Gear Guides & More‚õµOur Catamaranhttps://www.gonewiththewynns.com/curiosity-sailboatüì∑ Photo & Video Gear üì∑https://www.gonewiththewynns.com/photo-video-gear üì± UPDATES on Social üì±  INSTAGRAM: https://instagram.com/the_wynns/ FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/GoneWithTheWynns üìßEMAIL notifications, so you never miss a videoüç¶http://bit.ly/gwtw-socialüé∂ MUSIC for vids. 2 Months Free:  https://bit.ly/artlist-GWTWArtists ‚Äì Lance Conrad, Captain Qubz, Cosmonkey, Aves, Balloon Planet, SunRiver, The Huntsüé® Creative Assets for Vids (SFX, Templates & Presets):  - https://bit.ly/motion-array-GWTW üéΩGET YOUR SWAG ON:  https://gonewiththewynns.teemill.com/üíØFREE ways to support our productionshttp://bit.ly/join-gwtw----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------WE‚ÄôRE JASON AND NIKKI WYNN.  A couple of explorers, modern-day documentarians, and cultivators of curiosity.We‚Äôve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011. Why?  Because curiosity is the key to unlocking life.  It pushes us outside our comfort zone, softens our assumptions, and helps us embrace the great unknown.  The more we let our curiosity lead the way, the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us.Things We're Most Curious About:GETTING OFF-GRID Our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land.  So self-reliance and sustainable living are a must.  We've learned heaps about renewable energy, managing waste, creating safe drinking water and foraging for food.  We carefully manage our resources and we‚Äôre always looking for new and better ways to do so.  TALKING TO STRANGERSPeople are busy (even on remote islands) and travelers are a dime a dozen.  It takes time to talk to strangers, and even more time to have a real connection.  Going the extra mile to get to know someone is a commitment. Which is why these are our most treasured experiences.  Setting off into the world with curiosity as our guide and nature as our compass.  We talk to strangers and accept hospitality without fear or reservations.  Both giving and receiving.ALTERNATIVE LIVINGThese are people who are doing things differently. Forgoing the mainstream, seeking freedom and living on the margins. Creative, unique and inspiring people who challenge our ideas of home and community.Our journey is ever-evolving but the mission remains the same: #CultivateCuriosityTimestamps if you like to Jump Around:00:00 Building a Boat From Dream to Reality00:31 Our First Sail with Only 202:24 Learning to Sail the HH4404:52 Sailing in the Philippines06:31 How is the HH44 Sailing Upwind?09:06 So Much Wind - Ambil Island10:16 30 kts Headwind in a Narrow Pass13:17 BIG WAVES Sailing in 35 Knots of Wind on the Beam15:57 Crossing the Invisible Wind Line18:26 Flying the Massive Reacher Sail20:40 Sailing to Apo Reef Natural Park23:20 Mooring Ball Mistake25:50 Diving the Wild Apo Reef----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#BoatLife #Catamaran #TravelVlog #DigitalNomad #LifeStyle #Sailboats ¬© Gone With the Wynns 2024

column16: Get a browser that‚Äôs literally better at everything: https://operagx.gg/TankFishRoblox The Strongest Battlegrounds is a Roblox fighting game based on the anime One Punch Man. It is a free-for-all arena fight where skill and mastery are everything. Each character has 4 normal moves, and when you deal enough damage, you can unlock your ultimate, which gives you another set of more powerful moves. There are currently 8 different characters in the game, with 1 work in progress and one for private servers only. Their moves are based on their anime/manga counterparts and each has different playstyles, combos and techs that players will need to learn to be pro. I will try to showcase as many good combos and tips in this video as possible.The strongest hero is based on Saitama. You have no ranged attacks nor gap closers, so landing the first m1 will be the most difficult. After that, there are many combos and techs available to deal a ton of damage. His ultimate charges twice as fast but can only use 1 move per ultimate. Hero Hunter is based on Garou. He only has 3 offensive moves with a counter. However, his moves deal high damage and are easy to combo extends. The favorite character for the try hard sweaty gamers out there.Destructive Cyborg is based on Genos. He is very versatile but can be blocked or countered very easily since the moves have a predictable delay. His ultimates have a lot of area damage, GREAT at make everyone on the map mad. Deadly Ninja is based on Speed-o'-Sound Sonic. He is the perfect character for kill stealing and being annoying. It‚Äôs not the most fun character to play, but it‚Äôs very unfun to play against.Brutal Demon is based on Metal Bat. He has a lot of move variations and can adapt to many different situations. His ultimate bar charges when he takes damage, so you can have fun even if you are a noob.Blade Master is based on Atomic Samurai. His combos are easy to start but difficult to finish. He has a very strong ultimate, so try to get good and get it ASAP.Wild Psychic is based on Tatsumaki / Fubuki. It is currently not finished, but she‚Äôs super annoying to play against. She pulls you, pushes you and seals you under a rock. Good for teamers.Sorcerer is based on Gojo Satoru. He is only available to the private server owner. He is invincible and one-shots everyone. So yeah, just like the other Roblox In A Nutshell videos, I will attempt to show everything The Strongest Battleground has to offer. Like always, this Roblox video is filled with a crapload of dumb jokes and dead memes and takes the form of funny moments/funny montage/edits. The game will have new updates in the future, and I might play it again. Hit the like and the subscribe button. If you enjoyed this video, click the bell icon and don't forget to comment.----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------This video contains a crap load of dead memes and bad jokes. Viewer discretion advised.----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Be sure to leave a like if you enjoyed this Roblox video!Thanks for watching!Like and subscribe for more Roblox The Strongest Battlegrounds and other funny videos.Play Roblox The Strongest Battlegrounds: https://www.roblox.com/games/10449761463-Discord: https://discord.gg/3PN3JBNe6w-Twitter: https://twitter.com/TankFishYTRoblox The Strongest Battlegrounds In A Nutshell: The Duality Of Man - Tank Fish - Fish Tank#roblox #robloxedit #robloxmemes #robloxedits #robloxgames Roblox- The Strongest Battlegrounds: Roblox anime fighting game based on One Punch Man, train & fight others to be the strongest.What is ROBLOX? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It‚Äôs unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 8 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX ‚Äî interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything ‚Äî be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer ‚ÄúCapture the Flag‚Äù game or some other, yet¬≠to¬≠be¬≠dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (‚ÄúROBUX‚Äù). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

column2: Boosie Shows Boosie Town: New Batman Mansion & 4 Homes for His Kids on Property (Full Interview)
column8: VladTV|DJ Vlad|Interview|Hip-Hop|Rap|News|Gossip|Rumors|Drama
column16: Boosie recently hosted an interview on his 88-acre property, revealing his ambitious construction and development plans. The property, to be called Boosie Town, will consist of a Batman Mansion as the main house, four homes for his children, and a container mansion made with 40-ft cube containers. In the summer, his kids, ranging from 15 to 18 years old, will live in the houses independently to learn self-reliance. His plans also include a third swimming pool, a subdivision gate, and a golf cart track through the woods. Each two-story house will be uniquely designed with different features like glass or steel balconies and varied room configurations. Boosie is yet to finalize the cost of building these homes and is considering securing funding from investors in Saudi Arabia to construct more homes on the land in the future.He also showcased his nearly completed 'Batman Mansion.' The mansion features a Batman-inspired decor along with a customized pool table, marble island kitchen, four-and-a-half bedrooms, a personal theater with an LCD screen, and a dedicated yoga room, among other luxury amenities. The once-dense forest area on the property now features a golfing green, with more houses planned for development. On having too much space in the mansion, Boosie plans to consider Airbnb for parts of the mansion. The construction project is expected to be ready in about four months, potentially by June or July. Notably, 'Boosie Town' has inspired a host of upcoming artists, with Boosie revealing his continued plans to develop the property.
